A test for a DPPH free-radical scavenging effect was carried out according to Mensor and others59. A fresh sample of lettuce of 1 g was taken and crushed in 20 ml Methanol. The samples were centrifuged at 4 °C for 20 min at 10,000 rpm. A mixture of 1 mL of extract solution and 3.9 mL of DPPH was kept in the dark for 30 min. A UV–VIS Spectrophotometer (Spectra Max M2, Molecular Devices, USA) was used to record the absorbance of the reaction mixture at the 517 nm wavelength. The percentage of DPPH inhibition was computed as follows:Scavenging effect%DPPH inhibition=1-A1/A0]×100,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
