				\begin{document}$${\text{Scavenging effect }}\left( {\% {\text{ DPPH inhibition}}} \right) \, = {1 } - \, \left( {{\text{A}}_{{1}} /{\text{A}}_{0} } \right)] \times {1}00,$$\end{document}where A1 = Sample absorbance reading at 517 nm, A0 = Blank absorbance reading at 517 nm, Methanol (95%) was used as a blank. The results were presented in µmol Trolox/g FW.
